r s BC-BBA-ANGNOTE-LADN-(SLA     08-04 0319
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGNOTE-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SALMON JOINS THE FUN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND _ Darin Erstad and Troy Glaus went to the All-Star
game, Garret Anderson set his career-high for homers in a season,
Mo Vaughn was Mo Vaughn, hitting around .300 and hitting his share
of homers.
</P>
<P>
   Tim Salmon was frustrated.
</P>
<P>
   But now, the Anaheim Angels cleanup hitter has joined the party.
Even if it's at a time when many of the others are coming back to
earth, Salmon is hitting the ball like he knew _ hoped _ he could.
</P>
<P>
   Salmon will take an 11-game hitting streak into tonight's game
against the Indians. During those 11 games, he's hitting .500 (22
for 44). In the just-concluded series against the Tigers, Salmon
went 10 for 12, including hits in his past six consecutive at-bats.
</P>
<P>
   His average is up to .290, higher than Vaughn's (.287) and
Glaus' (.273). Salmon's power numbers are rising too _ he has 23
homers and 66 RBI.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm seeing the ball well,'' Salmon explained. ''I'm not
over-swinging and I'm putting the ball in play. The last two weeks
I've been swinging the bat better, and hitting the ball where it's
pitched.''
</P>
<P>
   Salmon soon will become the Angels' all-time home run leader. He
has 219, three short of Brian Downing's mark of 222.
</P>
<P>
   Vaughn is expected to be back in the lineup tonight after
leaving Wednesday's game early with a sore biceps muscle.
</P>
<P>
   Vaughn has slumped lately (3 for 31), and as a result is taking
extra batting practice. The extra swings in the cage may be the
cause for the muscle soreness.
</P>
<P>
   Pitcher Kent Mercker will start a rehab assignment for Single-A
Lake Elsinore tonight at Rancho Cucamonga. Mercker, who has
recovered from a brain hemorrhage suffered May 11, will need two
more rehab starts before he'll be ready to rejoin the big league
club.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
