<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OFFENSIVE SIGNING FOR BRUINS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BILLY WITZ  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA received an oral commitment late Tuesday
night from Collin Barker, considered one of the best of a bumper
crop of Texas offensive linemen in the class of 2001.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-8, 305-pound Barker, from Wortham, Texas, made an
unofficial visit to UCLA last week and also took unofficial trips
to Notre Dame and Michigan. He also considered Ohio State, Georgia
and Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Barker is the eighth player to commit to UCLA and the third
linemen, joining 6-foot-7, 275-pound Bob Cleary of Temescal Canyon
and 6-foot-8, 320-pound Ed Blanton of Napa.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-04-00 0136EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
