</P>
<P>
   GIANTS-INTERNET (San Francisco) _ The seventh-inning stretch is
coming up at Pac Bell Park and you realize it's been more than two
hours since you last logged in. Like a left-hander coming in from
the bullpen, relief is here. Giants fans now have limited access to
the Internet at one of five ``Web Stations'' at the park, making it
the first major league baseball stadium in the nation to provide
such a service. By VICTORIA COLLIVER. (also filed in the ``s''
category.)
</P>
<P>
