the mollusk family. They aren't as revered as oysters and aren't as
common as clams. But they're there, by the thousands, filling
bouillabaisse bowls and adding color to paellas. But mussels are
good for more than just adding body to mixed seafood dishes.
Mussels are also tasty on their own. By RUTH FANTASIA.
</P>
