   GRAND HOTEL_ I fell in love with Grand Hotel 30 years ago. The
hotel today still matches the picture I've kept in my mind's eye;
the wonderful front porch with its rocking chairs, cozy tables and
spectacular views of the gardens, grounds and lakes is the same.
Built in 1887 by two railroads and a steamship company eager to
attract Victorian travelers, it includes 1.5 million feet of
Michigan white pine. (Swartz, Palm Beach Post) Art includes a
2-column color photo of Grand Hotel.
