<P>
   ROCK-CLIMBING _ In rock climbing circles, that's the standard
ready-to-go signal at the start of an ascent. But it also could be
the rallying cry of the small but die-hard corps for whom climbing
has become a religion. We analyze why people climb and list
essentials for getting a leg up on this complex pastime. (Hamilton,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ ATLANTA _ Building a door _ a front entry door,
not a cabinet door _ is something I've thought about, but never
even got close to doing. However, the arrival of a new book from
Sterling, ``Doormaking: A Do-It-Yourself Guide,'' by John Birchard,
may get me going again. (Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HOME &AMP; GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   KIDS-FLOWERSHOP _ GRAND JUNCTION, Colo. _ We didn't know what it
was called or even exactly what we sold, all we knew is we had a
flower shop and it was the best flower shop anywhere. As kids, my
older sister Kristi and I ran the shop together out of our
grandparents' back yard of lush green grass, trees of all kinds,
vegetables, berries, and most striking of all _ flowers. ``We spent
hours in that garden,'' Kristi remembered. ``Time stood still when
we were out there.'' We spent many afternoons walking along the
garden paths talking to our imaginary customers about the different
flowers that were available.
</P>
