<P>
   RELIGION-SAMESEX _ The proverbial Wisdom of Solomon is often
needed for the Church to honor its traditions and do the right
thing. Splitting hairs, but not their church, Episcopalians have
done just that. (Gushee, Palm Beach Post). 14.
</P>
<P>
   MOMS-IN-TOUCH _DAYTON, Ohio _ Just because school prayer has
been deep-sixed by the United States Supreme Court doesn't mean
that parents can't offer up a supplication or two. Moms in Touch
International (MITI) is a group of mothers who believe that prayer
makes a difference. Individual chapters consisting of of two or
more moms meet once a week to pray for their children and the
schools they attend. Members believe that prayer is a way to
surround children with a spiritual presence even while they're at
school. (Dayton Daily News). 15. WITH PHOTOS.
