</P>
<P>
   KIDS-FLOWERSHOP _ GRAND JUNCTION, Colo. _ We didn't know what it
was called or even exactly what we sold, all we knew is we had a
flower shop and it was the best flower shop anywhere. As kids, my
older sister Kristi and I ran the shop together out of our
grandparents' back yard of lush green grass, trees of all kinds,
vegetables, berries, and most striking of all _ flowers. ``We spent
hours in that garden,'' Kristi remembered. ``Time stood still when
we were out there.'' We spent many afternoons walking along the
garden paths talking to our imaginary customers about the different
flowers that were available. (Grand Junction Daily Sentinel)
</P>
