<P>
   FBN-COWBOYS-MILES _ TOKYO _ Dave Campo calls it a business trip.
The Dallas Cowboys have not gone to Japan to sample Far East
cuisine or climb Mount Fuji. The only thing on Campo's mind is
improving a football team that hardly resembled world-beaters in
their preseason opener. ``This is what I call a real road game,''
Campo said, referring to the American Bowl game against the Atlanta
Falcons Saturday night at the Tokyo Dome. The Cowboys had better
get used to traveling. No team will fly more miles this season than
the Cowboys, the unofficial ambassadors of the NFL. Including
preseason, the Cowboys will travel 31,020 miles. Seattle is second
with 30,218 and San Francisco third at 29,928. By contrast,
Tennessee travels a league-low 8,498 miles. Dallas will always be
among the NFL leaders in travel miles, partly because they have an
owner who likes to market his team around the world. (Cantu, Austin
American-Statesman). 19
</P>
