Speedway that calls IMS the ``Racing Capital of the World'' is now
accurate. Until last year, the declaration was debatable. This
year's Brickyard 400 is Saturday, but IMS officials have Sept. 24
circled on their calendars. That's when the fabled track moves to a
higher level _ an international level _ by hosting a Formula One
race, the United States Grand Prix, for the first time. (Lance,
Dayton Daily News). Art includes a 2-column color photo of the
pagoda at IMS and a 1-column photo of track president Tony George.
