<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-BIASCASE _ Attorneys for plaintiffs in the Coca-Cola racial
discrimination lawsuit will be back before a federal judge Friday.
A legal team headed by Florida attorney Willie Gary is trying to
get the judge in the case to compel another team headed by
Washington attorney Cyrus Mehri to turn over its files on
plaintiffs who left Mehri to be represented by Gary. The judge may
rule. (This battle is unrelated to the $1.5 billion suit Gary has
filed against Coke on behalf of four women employees.) (Rankin,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   HDEPOT-SUIT _ Home Depot has agreed to pay $500,000 to a New
Jersey couple whose 6-year-old son suffered brain damage in a 1997
store accident. According to the Philadelphia Inquirer, Brandon
Ryan was struck by at lease one of nine 20-pound boxes that fell
eight feet from a shelf. The settlement includes $100,000 for the
father, James Ryan, who suffered emotional distress after
witnessing the accident. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 6.
</P>
