<P>
   TALISMAN-CHIC (Undated) _ There is a vastly expanding tribe of
New Yorkers who, trusting nothing to chance, attempt to ward off
evil or beguile the gods by draping themselves in exotic beads and
talismans. Beetles and Buddhas, scarabs, pentagrams and pale pink
quartz _ any of these may function as a symbol of sincere religious
belief. But in the age of Spirituality Lite, they are also likely
to attest to the wearer's inner grooviness. By Ruth La Ferla.
</P>
