   (With photo)
</P>
<P>
   DOTCOM-BLUES (Undated) _ ``Our multimillion-dollar dot-com
folded,'' writes Timothy Jack Ward, ``and all I got was this lousy
T-shirt ... Everyone at Posh&AMP;Sticks got one, the day our enigmatic
_ let's face it, odd _ name was announced last January. Now it is a
bittersweet souvenir from the rush for the elusive e-commerce
mother lode. Don't get me wrong: I loved the name and was proud to
wear it on my chest. We gave this our best shot, but we are
toast.''
