   COXNET FOCUS 0805: COLOMBIA GRIPPED IN FEAR _ Bands of heavily
armed guerrillas and right-wing paramilitary groups roam the
countryside, warring against each other over ideology and control
of the illegal drug trade. Rural peasants, caught in the middle,
have fled by the thousands, their homes destroyed, businesses
ruined, their children lured or taken at gunpoint to join the
groups of fighters. Colombia is a nation living in fear and
uncertainty. Few are untouched by the country's troubles.
