   HELEN-THOMAS (Philadelphia) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush accepted
the Republican presidential nomination with a soaring speech that
might be summed up as ``promises, promises, promises.'' Actually,
he almost sounded like a Democrat _ and he swiped a few pages out
of President Clinton's book. But that's only fair. After all,
Clinton hijacked the GOP agenda with his call for a balanced
budget, welfare reform and cutting the national debt. By HELEN
