make no mistake, the Republican Party was also on trial. By CLAY
ROBISON.
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ The relationship between the
George W. Bush's Republicans and Bill Clinton is a fascinating
study in contradictions. On the one hand, GOP leaders express their
disgust with the president's behavior and speak longingly of having
a president worthy of their respect. On the other hand, their
decision to transform the GOP's image by opening the party's doors
widely to African Americans, Hispanics and gays copies the type of
strategy that twice won the presidency for Clinton and the
Democrats. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (For release Sunday, Aug 6.)
(Already filed.)
</P>
