   &UR; AUTOS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ABOUTCARS-MERCEDES (Undated) _ The Mercedes-Benz brochure of the
1980s described the marque's philosophy thus: A Mercedes should not
inspire aggressive driving, but if you find yourself in a bind _
say, roaring into a tight turn too fast _ the car will get you
through. That, at least, was the gist. The Mercedes was an
automotive Clark Kent, serious and sedate, but ready to fling off
its eyeglasses and soar to the rescue. There is nothing
mild-mannered about the Mercedes-Benz of today. By Serge Schmemann.
</P>
