   ROCK-FAN-FAMILIES (Undated) _ The rock concert, once a raucous
and often drug-filled rite of initiation into American adolescence,
is slowly becoming a family affair. Parents of teenagers and
younger children _ ones who, in their day, treasured concerts as
escapes from the parental clutches _ now want to share the
experience with their own offspring. It is increasingly easier to
do this as the musical tastes of the generations meld _ the 40-plus
group of Americans now buy more rock albums than those 15 to 24 _
and as concerts have been tamed by commercial sponsors to be as
clean as Broadway musicals. By Leslie Kaufman.
