</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 4, 2000 -- GOP-BUSH-RDP -- A
woman, part of the crew cleaning up the floor following the
Republican National Convention, gathers signs just after midnight,
Friday. Speaking to a jubilant final session of the convention, Gov.
George W. Bush, the GOP's presidential candidate, argued that "times
of plenty" were times to solve major problems, not to sit back and
relax. (Andrea Mohin/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) CHICAGO -- Aug. 4, 2000 -- GORE-2 -- Upon arrival to
Chicago on a campaign swing, vice President Al Gore stopped by the
International Association of Firefighters Convention and greeted
members of Engine 13, including Lucky, the Dalmation, who Tipper
"commanded" to stand. Gore ended his weeklong vacation Friday and
returned to the presidential campaign trail in Chicago. (Paul
Hosefros/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) CHICAGO -- Aug. 4, 2000 -- GORE -- Vice President Al
Gore, accompanied by his wife Tipper, waves on arriving to the
International Association of Firefighters Convention, Friday. Gore
ended his weeklong vacation Friday and returned to the presidential
campaign trail in Chicago. (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
</P>
