<HEADLINE>
HINGIS TOP SEED FOR ESTYLE.COM CLASSC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICH HAMMOND  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANHATTAN BEACH, Calif. _ Martina Hingis received the top seed
and a first-round bye when the singles draw for next week's
estyle.com Classic was announced Friday at Manhattan Country Club.
</P>
<P>
   Hingis headlines a strong field which also features four former
tournament champions _ Lindsay Davenport, Conchita Martinez, Monica
Seles and Serena Williams _ and a total of seven players ranked in
the world top 10.
</P>
<P>
   The 32-player tournament will begin on Monday with first-round
matches and conclude Sunday, Aug. 13.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is definitely a very tough field,'' said Barbara Schett,
who drew seventh-seeded Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario in the first round.
``Every round is a challenge. You could win a couple rounds, but
you could also lose in the first round.''
</P>
<P>
   Hingis, Davenport, Seles and Martinez, the top four seeds,
respectively, each received a first-round bye. Fifth-seeded
Williams will face Ruxandra Dragomir, sixth-seeded Nathalie Tauziat
will meet one of the weekend qualifiers and Sandrine Testud will
face Elena Likhovtseva in other first-round matches.
</P>
<P>
   The draw sets up possible semifinals of Hingis against Williams
or Martinez and Davenport against Seles, but Hingis' half of the
draw also includes last year's surprise Wimbledon standout,
Alexandra Stevenson, who received a wild-card berth, and Amy
Frazier, who stunned Hingis on Thursday in the quarterfinals of the
Acura Classic.
</P>
<P>
   Anke Huber, who would have been the seventh seed in the
tournament, withdrew Friday because of tendinitis in her elbow.
</P>
<P>
   First-round matches will begin Monday at 10 a.m. PDT, and the
schedule will be determined on Sunday. Single-day tickets cost
$12-$75 and series passes can be purchased for $120-$350. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
